						               													<description>Update: Toast! was not funded on Kickstarter, but the design was taken up by Horrible Games and developed into Raise Your Goblets.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Toast! is themed around ruthless medieval nobles trying to poison each other during the toasts at a royal function. The King has decreed a bizarre etiquette to be followed, in an attempt to discourage this behaviour. However, instead it has just turned the practice into an art and a sport, with each (surviving) noble having developed a particular expertise.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a round of play, goblets are arranged in a circle in the middle of the table, one in front of each player, such that players can&amp;rsquo;t see their contents. Players take turns to secretly place wine, poison or antidote tokens into the goblets,  switching the goblets around, or using their characters special abilities. Each player has a target, and their aim is to ensure that, when the round is ended by someone calling for the Toast and the players all &amp;lsquo;drink&amp;rsquo;, their target&amp;rsquo;s goblet is poisoned and theirs is safe!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game supports 2-12 players. The main rules are for 4-6 players, there are special rules to extend up to 12 players (where pairs of players play as a noble and their wine-taster), and there is a separate game mode for 2-3 players (a sort of Russian Roulette with goblets).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
